The assertThat method can be used to test properties of collections. E.g.

  assertThat(aList, containsElement(&quot;foo&quot;))

The collections interfaces guarantee that Set and List have meaningful
implementations of equals, so it&#39;s also valid to test for equality:

  import static java.utils.Arrays.asList;
  ...

  assertThat(aList, equalTo(asList(&quot;foo&quot;, &quot;bar&quot;, &quot;baz&quot;)));

